      • object2ShortEntrySet

        public ObjectSet<Object2ShortMap.Entry<K>> object2ShortEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Object2ShortMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Object2ShortMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        object2ShortEntrySet in interface Object2ShortMap<K>
        Returns:
        a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
